      Over the past two years, I have been studying attitudes toward government by inviting myself into coffee klatches among a wide variety of people across the state of Wisconsin. I have been surprised by the pervasiveness of the sentiment that government does not listen. All levels of government need to become more open, and not just by communicating outward (e.g., providing more information, holding public hearings). All levels of government need to send public officials out into the public to meet with people in the course of their daily lives to listen to their concerns and become acquainted with their lifestyles.<br/><br/>Kathy Cramer Walsh<br/>Madison, Wisconsin

                  
    </td>
  </tr>


